-- China'S Stocks Fall as Smaller Companies Decline on Rising Lending Costs
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-12-23T06:44:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-23/china-s-stocks-fall-as-smaller-companies-decline-on-rising-lending-costs.html
China’s stocks dropped for a second
day on concern rising lending costs will hurt the growth outlook
for the nation’s smaller companies.  The Shanghai Composite Index, which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, slid 16.44, or 0.6 percent, to      
2,861.46 as of 2:38 p.m. The CSI Smallcap 500 Index lost 1.6 
percent.                                   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
